quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  10,43,"Some of them look fixedly at you; but can you make the blind see, bereft as they are of sight"
  10,44,"Surely, God does not wrong people at all, but people wrong themselves"
  10,45,"And on the Day when He shall gather them together, it will seem to them as if they had not tarried in the world longer than an hour of a day. They will recognize one another; lost indeed will be those who considered it a lie that they were destined to meet God, and did not follow the right path"
  10,46,"Whether We show you something of what We have promised them or cause you to die [before that], to Us they shall return. God is Witness to all that they do"
  10,47,"Every nation has a messenger. Once their messenger has come, judgement will be passed upon them in all fairness and they will not be wronged"
  10,48,"They say, \"When will this promise come to pass -- if you speak the truth"
  10,49,"Say, \"I have no control over any harm or benefit to myself, except by the will of God. For every people, however, there is an appointed term. When the end of their term arrives, they cannot postpone it for an hour, nor can they advance it"
  10,50,"Say, \"If His punishment comes upon you in the dead of night, or by the light of day, how will the guilty escape it"
  10,51,"Will you believe in it only after it has overtaken you, although it was your wish to hurry it on"
  10,52,"Then the evil-doers will be told, \"Taste the everlasting punishment. Have you not been rewarded according to your deeds"
  10,53,"They enquire of you if this will really happen. Tell them, \"Yes, by my Lord. Most certainly it will happen, and you cannot avert it"